      • graphBuilder

        public static java.lang.StringBuffer graphBuilder(int v,
                                                  int e,
                                                  int min,
                                                  int max)
        This method creates a 3 token representation of a graph.
        Parameters:
        v - The number of vertices in the graph
        e - The number of edges leaving each vertice
        min - The lowerbound on the capacity value of each edge
        max - The upperbound on the capacity value of each edge
        Returns:
        A string buffer, each line contains 3 tokens corresponding to a directed edge: the tail, the head, and the capacity.
